Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3}(chopped into 2cm wedges, peeling optional). Peel and grate the @garlic{3}(peeled and grated with a garlic press). Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, toss with garlic, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{2}(trimmed then halved lengthways, no need to peel and chopped into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons). Pop onto a large (lined) baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer then roast on the middle shelf of the oven until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Trim the @green beans{75%g}. Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot, add the green beans and fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{to taste} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until the green beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Wipe the pan and return to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Season the @21 Day Aged Irish Sirloin Steak{250%g} with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Once hot, fry the sirloin until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare. Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it more well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when outside is browned.

Once cooked, remove from the pan, cover and allow to rest.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with @butter{2%tbsp}. Add @water{50%ml} and @mustard{2%sachets} to the pan. Stir to form a sauce and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Simmer until reduced to desired thickness. In a #small bowl{}, mix the @aioli{1%sachet} and @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> Tip: Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if it becomes too thick.

Thinly slice the sirloin and divide between plates. Next, plate up the garlic wedges, carrots and green beans. Drizzle the mustard sauce over the steak. Serve aioli alongside.